Day 2 â€“ Java Collections + Concurrency + Java 11/17 Features
Topic 1: HashMap vs ConcurrentHashMap
âœ… HashMap
Not thread-safe

Allows null key and multiple null values

Fails with ConcurrentModificationException if modified during iteration

java
Copy
Edit
Map<String, String> map = new HashMap<>();
map.put(null, "value");  // Allowed
âœ… ConcurrentHashMap
Thread-safe (uses internal segment locking)

Doesnâ€™t allow null key or null value

Uses fail-safe iterator â€” no exception when modifying during iteration

java
Copy
Edit
Map<String, String> cmap = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
cmap.put("A", "1");
cmap.put("B", "2");

for (String key : cmap.keySet()) {
    cmap.put("C", "3");  // Works fine â€” no exception
}
