âœ… DAY 1 â€“ Topic 2: Reverse Sentence Word by Word
ğŸ” Problem:
Reverse the words in a sentence, not characters.

ğŸ§ª Input:
java
Copy
Edit
"I am learning Java"
âœ… Output:
java
Copy
Edit
"Java learning am I"
ğŸ’¡ Suggested Approach (Two options):
Option 1 â€“ Split & reverse loop:
java
Copy
Edit
String input = "I am learning Java";
String[] words = input.split(" ");
StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();

for (int i = words.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    result.append(words[i]);
    if (i != 0) result.append(" ");
}
System.out.println(result.toString());
Option 2 â€“ Two-pointer in-place swap:
java
Copy
Edit
String input = "I am learning Java";
String[] words = input.split(" ");
int left = 0, right = words.length - 1;

while (left < right) {
    String temp = words[left];
    words[left] = words[right];
    words[right] = temp;
    left++;
    right--;
}
System.out.println(String.join(" ", words));
