ChatGPT said:
Perfect, Ajinkya! Now letâ€™s get into a classic interview favorite:

âœ… Day 2 â€“ Topic 3: Thread-Safe Singleton Pattern
Interviewers often ask:

"How do you implement a Singleton in a thread-safe way in Java?"

âš ï¸ Problem with Basic Singleton:
java
Copy
Edit
public class Singleton {
    private static Singleton instance;

    private Singleton() {} // private constructor

    public static Singleton getInstance() {
        if (instance == null) {
            instance = new Singleton();  // âŒ Not thread-safe
        }
        return instance;
    }
}
If two threads call getInstance() at the same time, both could create separate objects â€” not a true Singleton!

âœ… Approach 1: Synchronized Method
java
Copy
Edit
public class Singleton {
    private static Singleton instance;

    private Singleton() {}

    public static synchronized Singleton getInstance() {
        if (instance == null) {
            instance = new Singleton();  // âœ… Thread-safe, âŒ Slow
        }
        return instance;
    }
}
Simple

Slower because synchronization happens on every call

âœ… Approach 2: Double-Checked Locking (Best in Java 11+)
java
Copy
Edit
public class Singleton {
    private static volatile Singleton instance;

    private Singleton() {}

    public static Singleton getInstance() {
        if (instance == null) {
            synchronized (Singleton.class) {
                if (instance == null) {
                    instance = new Singleton();  // âœ… Efficient & safe
                }
            }
        }
        return instance;
    }
}
volatile ensures visibility of changes

synchronized is used only once, when instance is null

âœ… Approach 3: Holder Class (Lazy, Thread-safe, Best Practice)
java
Copy
Edit
public class Singleton {

    private Singleton() {}

    private static class Holder {
        private static final Singleton INSTANCE = new Singleton();
    }

    public static Singleton getInstance() {
        return Holder.INSTANCE;
    }
}
Uses class loading mechanism

Thread-safe without synchronization

Recommended by Effective Java

Which version do you want to try in your IDE?
